# TSX “other” templates (from `tsx_other.json`)

Summarizes **130** files that are **`.tsx`** but **not** under **`**/components/**`** (see [`.agents/file-lists/tsx_other.json`](../file-lists/tsx_other.json)): **routes/pages**, **app shell**, **entry** files, and **feature-level** TSX not classified as components.

## Inventory snapshot

| Fact | Typical value |
| --- | --- |
| Path depth (median) | 7 segments |
| Common roots | `app/pages` (~82%), `app/features` (~8%), `app/utils` (~5%) |
| Largest slice | `app/pages/Result/...` (~76%) |
| Root files | `App.tsx`, `Index.tsx`, `root.tsx`, `entry.client.tsx`, `entry.server.tsx` |

## Roles

| Kind | Examples |
| --- | --- |
| Route / page module | `app/pages/Result/Result.tsx`, route feature shells |
| Renderers | `ResultDesktopRenderer.tsx`, `ResultAppRenderer.tsx` |
| App shell | `app/root.tsx`, `app/App.tsx` |
| Entry | `entry.client.tsx`, `entry.server.tsx` |

## Template — page with loader data

```typescript
import type { ReactElement } from "react";
import type { ServerComponentPropsType } from "types/ServerComponentProps.type";

import type { PageLoaderDataType } from "./types/PageLoaderData.type";

type PageProps = ServerComponentPropsType<PageLoaderDataType>;

export default function Page({ loaderData }: PageProps): ReactElement {
  return <div>{loaderData.title}</div>;
}
```

## Conventions

- **Default export** for the routable page component is common.
- **`memo`** when the team already uses it for expensive page trees (see **`Result.tsx`** pattern).
- Compose **device renderers** via hooks like **`useDeviceOutputRenderer`** instead of duplicating branches.

